{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we suggest that LLMs could be adopted as powerful cognitive prosthetics, able to afford self-corrective and explorative behaviours within a structured learning embedding such as the 'prepared environment' of the Montessori classroom.",
    "The case of online training of LLMs has been explored by Microsoft's Tay, which was left to learn from online Twitter interactions and was, somewhat unsurprisingly, very quickly coaxed into parroting misogynist and racist nonsense(Hunt,",
    "2016).2 Although, this might be unprecise, and maybe unfair to parrots who are quite able to autonomously engage with world affordances.",
    "See, e.g., Pepperberg, (2006); Colbert- White et al., (2011); Auersperg & von Bayern, (2019).",
    "For a general account, see: LeDoux et al., 2023."
  ]
}